guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://www.morgancheng.com/?p=1022") (description nil "史蒂夫.乔布斯的演讲水平一流，写作技巧也相当了得，在这篇Thoughts on Flash（看不了英文版可以看中文版）中，乔布斯从各个方面解析为什么Apple放弃Flash，让人不得不相信，不让Flash存在于iPod/iPhone/iPad上是利国利民的正确选择。\n\n\n乔布斯的遣词造句很巧妙，字面之下有更深含义，比如这句：\nToday the two companies still work together to serve their joint creative customers – Mac users buy around half of Adobe’s Creative Suite products – but beyond that there are few joint interests.\nMac的用户买了Adobe一半的CS产品，是我的粉丝养活了你Adobe，是你Adobe依赖于我，而不是我乔布斯大人依赖你。\n还有这句：\nWebKit has been widely adopted. Google uses it for Android&#8217;s browser, Palm uses it, Nokia uses it, and RIM (Blackberry) has [...]\n\n\n相关文章：<ol><li><a href='http://www.morgancheng.com/2010/05/01/microsoft-slate-project-not-so-smooth/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: 风雨飘摇的微软平板电脑计划'>风雨飘摇的微软平板电脑计划</a></li><li><a href='http://www.morgancheng.com/2010/04/14/war-of-platform/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: 平台之战'>平台之战</a></li><li><a href='http://www.morgancheng.com/2010/03/21/will-ie9-bring-microsoft-back-to-top/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: IE9能否让微软重回巅峰？'>IE9能否让微软重回巅峰？</a></li><li><a href='http://www.morgancheng.com/2010/02/20/%e5%be%ae%e8%bd%af%e5%b0%86%e8%ae%a9%e6%ac%a7%e6%b4%b2%e7%94%a8%e6%88%b7%e8%87%aa%e5%b7%b1%e9%80%89%e6%8b%a9%e6%b5%8f%e8%a7%88%e5%99%a8%ef%bc%9aie%e4%b8%a7%e5%a4%b1%e6%8d%86%e7%bb%91%e4%bc%98%e5%8a%bf/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: 微软将让欧洲用户自己选择浏览器：IE丧失捆绑优势'>微软将让欧洲用户自己选择浏览器：IE丧失捆绑优势</a></li><li><a href='http://www.morgancheng.com/2010/03/10/internet-100-years-later/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: 关注100年之后的互联网？'>关注100年之后的互联网？</a></li></ol>") (content:encoded nil "<p>史蒂夫.乔布斯的演讲水平一流，写作技巧也相当了得，在这篇<a href=\"http://www.apple.com/hotnews/thoughts-on-flash/\">Thoughts on Flash</a>（看不了英文版可以看<a href=\"http://cnbeta.com/articles/109919.htm\">中文版</a>）中，乔布斯从各个方面解析为什么Apple放弃Flash，让人不得不相信，不让Flash存在于iPod/iPhone/iPad上是利国利民的正确选择。</p><p><a href=\"http://www.morgancheng.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/applevsflash.jpg\"><img style=\"display: block; float: none; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; border: 0px;\" title=\"apple-vs-flash\" src=\"http://www.morgancheng.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/applevsflash_thumb.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"apple-vs-flash\" width=\"259\" height=\"152\" /></a></p><p><span id=\"more-1022\"></span></p><p>乔布斯的遣词造句很巧妙，字面之下有更深含义，比如这句：</p><blockquote><p>Today the two companies still work together to serve their joint creative customers – Mac users buy around half of Adobe’s Creative Suite products – but beyond that there are few joint interests.</p></blockquote><p>Mac的用户买了Adobe一半的CS产品，是我的粉丝养活了你Adobe，是你Adobe依赖于我，而不是我乔布斯大人依赖你。</p><p>还有这句：</p><blockquote><p>WebKit has been widely adopted. Google uses it for Android&#8217;s browser, Palm uses it, Nokia uses it, and RIM (Blackberry) has announced they will use it too. Almost every smartphone web browser other than Microsoft&#8217;s uses WebKit.</p></blockquote><p>大家都用Webkit，几乎所有的智能手机浏览器都用Webkit（我记得Opera不用Webkit)，除了微软的手机之外。这句话暗含的意思就是，Webkit已经是移动浏览器的事实霸主，要做成功的移动浏览器，就用Webkit，除非你想和Microsoft手机一样苟延残喘（Microsoft Phone你真要不蒸馒头争口气啊！）。</p><p>这次乔布斯真的是说得天衣无缝，让Flash几乎没法还嘴。不过就像我们喜欢看《黄飞鸿》喜欢看《叶问》，虽然黄飞鸿和叶问强大得不可战胜，但是我们还是喜欢看他们打，我们且看Flash和Adobe怎么打下去:)</p><p><script type=\"text/javascript\"></script><script type=\"text/javascript\"\nsrc=\"http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js\"></script></p><p>相关文章：</p><ol><li><a href='http://www.morgancheng.com/2010/05/01/microsoft-slate-project-not-so-smooth/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: 风雨飘摇的微软平板电脑计划'>风雨飘摇的微软平板电脑计划</a></li><li><a href='http://www.morgancheng.com/2010/04/14/war-of-platform/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: 平台之战'>平台之战</a></li><li><a href='http://www.morgancheng.com/2010/03/21/will-ie9-bring-microsoft-back-to-top/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: IE9能否让微软重回巅峰？'>IE9能否让微软重回巅峰？</a></li><li><a href='http://www.morgancheng.com/2010/02/20/%e5%be%ae%e8%bd%af%e5%b0%86%e8%ae%a9%e6%ac%a7%e6%b4%b2%e7%94%a8%e6%88%b7%e8%87%aa%e5%b7%b1%e9%8