ews/thoughts-on-flash/\">Thoughts on Flash</a>（看不了英文版可以看<a href=\"http://cnbeta.com/articles/109919.htm\">中文版</a>）中，乔布斯从各个方面解析为什么Apple放弃Flash，让人不得不相信，不让Flash存在于iPod/iPhone/iPad上是利国利民的正确选择。</p><p><a href=\"http://www.morgancheng.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/applevsflash.jpg\"><img style=\"display: block; float: none; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; border: 0px;\" title=\"apple-vs-flash\" src=\"http://www.morgancheng.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/applevsflash_thumb.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"apple-vs-flash\" width=\"259\" height=\"152\" /></a></p><p><span id=\"more-1022\"></span></p><p>乔布斯的遣词造句很巧妙，字面之下有更深含义，比如这句：</p><blockquote><p>Today the two companies still work together to serve their joint creative customers – Mac users buy around half of Adobe’s Creative Suite products – but beyond that there are few joint interests.</p></blockquote><p>Mac的用户买了Adobe一半的CS产品，是我的粉丝养活了你Adobe，是你Adobe依赖于我，而不是我乔布斯大人依赖你。</p><p>还有这句：</p><blockquote><p>WebKit has been widely adopted. Google uses it for Android’s browser, Palm uses it, Nokia uses it, and RIM (Blackberry) has announced they will use it too. Almost every smartphone web browser other than Microsoft’s uses WebKit.</p></blockquote><p>大家都用Webkit，几乎所有的智能手机浏览器都用Webkit（我记得Opera不用Webkit)，除了微软的手机之外。这句话暗含的意思就是，Webkit已经是移动浏览器的事实霸主，要做成功的移动浏览器，就用Webkit，除非你想和Microsoft手机一样苟延残喘（Microsoft Phone你真要不蒸馒头争口气啊！）。</p><p>这次乔布斯真的是说得天衣无缝，让Flash几乎没法还嘴。不过就像我们喜欢看《黄飞鸿》喜欢看《叶问》，虽然黄飞鸿和叶问强大得不可战胜，但是我们还是喜欢看他们打，我们且看Flash和Adobe怎么打下去:)</p><p><script type=\"text/javascript\"></script><script type=\"text/javascript\"\nsrc=\"http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js\"></script></p><p>相关文章：</p><ol><li><a href='http://www.morgancheng.com/2010/05/01/microsoft-slate-project-not-so-smooth/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: 风雨飘摇的微软平板电脑计划'>风雨飘摇的微软平板电脑计划</a></li><li><a href='http://www.morgancheng.com/2010/04/14/war-of-platform/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: 平台之战'>平台之战</a></li><li><a href='http://www.morgancheng.com/2010/03/21/w